  "text": "Another difficulty in evaluating the role of mast cells is connected with their presence and active participation in several, apart from tumorigenesis, physiological and pathological events, including reactions of immediate hypersensitivity. They are capable of processing antigens, phagocytosis, as well as producing and releasing biologically active factors, and, moreover, their surface is covered with many receptors and molecules reacting with various kinds of stimuli. Unfortunately, no human or animal model of a condition with an absolute lack of mast cells, which could help us understand their functions, has been recognized yet [CITATION_1] .",
